rComments: Favorite prof of the whole fall term - made me excited to go to class and was easy to follow along with the help of power point slides. Lots of weekly reading but also was not bad at all if you skipped a week or two or more.

One of the best professors at U of T. Great slides, amazing lectures that are funny, organized, focused and the topic and arguments are clearly outlined. Assignments really helped understand course material. He was very down to earth, answered questions clearly, and used a lot of personal examples when teaching. Also his tweets are the best.

Professor Gunitsky is an amazing lecturer. He explains things in detail and his lectures get easier to follow once you figure out his style. Has a sense of humour and cares for his students. Always asking us if we feel hot because the lecture hall can get pretty warm. Prof is not boring and has an amazing smile. Will definitely take another course
Great lecturer. His style is very conversational and engaging. The course content was interesting and readings drew from many different sources. Could not recommend more highly.

I love Professor Gunitsky! He was definitely my favourite professor from all the 2018 2nd year International Relations courses. His lectures were clear, structured, and engaging. I would definitely take him again. He isn't monotone, which makes him nice to listen to.
